ALIEN BREED 3D II

Captain Reynolds, the sole survivor of the Osiris hybrid break out, had been floating in space for weeks when the Earth Force Battle Cruiser heard the Escape Shuttles distress signal. With the Osiris complex destroyed and cruiser now making its way back to Earth, Reynolds lay unconscious in a high security medical unit. The Shuttles distress signal , however, had not only reached his saviours.... A huge dark shadow moved silently across the river of emptiness that is space. Progressing slowly toward the battle cruiser, using a cloaking system, making it invisible to sensors and tracking devices. Its vastness dwarfing one of Osiris many moons. In its relentless, silent orbit around the dark side of the planet, advancing mercilessly on its intended prey, having closed in on the cruiser the shadow lunged forward.

Reynolds awakes in the unfamiliar surroundings of the battle cruisers, medical unit. His head still spinning he looks around, everything is silent. He moves out into the corridor to find the outside door lock has been shot out, isolating the medical bay.

An unholy beast/like shriek echoes from the distance, Reynolds mind flickers with remembrance. The body of a dead soldier draws Reynolds attention. Reynolds face drains of colour with past memories he retrieves a pulse rifle from the corpse and glares into the dim distance... The nightmare starts once more.
MACHINE REQUIREMENTS

LOADING THE GAME

To run AB3DII from the game disks place disk one into you disk drive and power up your Amiga, insert disk two only when prompted and follow all on/screen instructions.
INSTALLATION TO HARDDRIVE

To install AB3DII to your harddrive place disk 2 into the disk drive and double click on the game icon, follow the on-screen instructions.

If your machine has only 2Mb of memory it is advisable to boot with no start-up sequence, this is done by holding down both mouse buttons when powering the Amiga and clicking on the Boot with no start-up sequence option.
THE GAME

You play as Captain Reynolds. After escaping the onslaught of the Osiris Complex you find yourself aboard the battle cruiser. You must make your way around to discover what has happened to the crew. How the breed had managed to get aboard, then follow your Instincts to take you to strange new environments. Each level has a specific task or mission to fulfil, with each successfully completed level you gain more knowledge of the Breeds overall objective.

AUTO MAP
2Meg version

Press Tab key to activate, this will pause the game and bring Up a map of the level you are playing, but only the areas you have uncovered will be displayed.

Press Tab key to activate, this will overlay the game screen with a map, zoom in and out with the F1 and F2 key. Move the position of the map by use of the Numeric Keypad as detailed in the controls section.
ANTI-GRAV PACK

In later levels you will find an Anti-Gravity Pack, you must find various fuel terminals to power the pack, beware as it only remains activated for a few seconds so use it when you really need to. To activate the fuelled Anti-Grav Pack press the 0 (jump) key on the numeric keypad.
